This paper is about object detection using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new approach for improving object detection accuracy, which involves adding deconvolution layers to the existing framework. This is a machine learning technique, which could also place the paper in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
